OL,3,GNorth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA chilly start with isolated
OL,6,Ffog patches. Sunny spells developing
OL,7,Ffor a while, but cloud slowly bubbling
OL,8,Fup allowing showers to develop. The
OL,9,Fshowers may become heavy and possibly
OL,10,Fthundery at times during the
OL,11,Fafternoon. Lighter winds than of late.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FDaytime showers easing this
OL,14,Fevening leaving a dry night with clear
OL,15,Fspells for a while. Turning chilly
OL,16,Fwith a patchy frost before further
OL,17,Fcloud arrives from the southwest by
OL,18,Fdawn.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
